  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\r\nWhen the same data is received from multiple gossip messages simultaneously, it's possible that we will spend time validating both of them, only for one of them to be eventually rejected as a duplicate after validation when it is actually recorded in received messages and find the other message there.\r\n\r\nThe window for this is fairly small as we check if the message is a duplicate before any validation occurs, but we can't record the result at that point because the message isn't yet valid.  We should investigate a system similar to `CacheableTaskQueue` (or possibly just use it) which supports deduplicating messages even prior to validation.",
